00:00:12.630 --> 00:00:14.160
students across the country find out

00:00:14.160 --> 00:00:15.299
where they're going to be placed for

00:00:15.299 --> 00:00:18.630
internship and residency they start

00:00:18.630 --> 00:00:20.550
applying early in the fall and they

00:00:20.550 --> 00:00:23.010
interview throughout the winter months

00:00:23.010 --> 00:00:23.590
and then

00:00:23.590 --> 00:00:26.140
they place their list of where they

00:00:26.140 --> 00:00:28.930
prefer and a rank list is submitted to

00:00:28.930 --> 00:00:31.090
a national database the computer

00:00:31.090 --> 00:00:32.650
basically lines up the programs with the

00:00:32.650 --> 00:00:34.450
students and then instead of having

00:00:34.450 --> 00:00:36.520
multiple offers and it'd be very

00:00:36.520 --> 00:00:38.710
confusing they find out what is matched

00:00:38.710 --> 00:00:40.390
how they matched up with the program and

00:00:40.390 --> 00:00:42.320
they get

00:00:42.320 --> 00:00:45.520
told where they're going basically

